cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.IR. 

The paper deals with instance segmentation, which is a computer vision problem, and proposes a novel framework for training with image-level labels. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves training a classifier and a fully supervised Mask R-CNN, which suggests that it may fall under the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper evaluates its method on a standard dataset, which could place it under cs.MM (Multimedia) or cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
